  "elementOrder": ["b-kicker", "b-question", "b-helps", "b-hurts"],
  "definitions": {
    "b-kicker": {
      "type": "elementHeading",
      "level": 6,
      "text": "THE CENTRAL DISTINCTION",
      "align": "left",
      "width": "hug",
      "height": "hug"
    },
    "b-question": {
      "type": "elementHeading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Motion reduces cognitive load when it communicates causality. It adds to it when it decorates.",
      "align": "left",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "marginBottom": "0.25rem",
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "slideUp",
        "viewport": {
          "amount": 0.2
        },
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "duration": 0.5,
            "delay": 0
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "b-helps": {
      "type": "elementRichText",
      "content": "### When Motion Helps\n\n- **Spatial continuity** — showing where an element came from or went to (e.g. a sheet sliding in from the side explains its place in a hierarchy)\n- **Causal feedback** — confirming that an action produced an effect\n- **State transition** — showing what changed between two states without requiring comparison\n- **Orientation** — anchoring the user within a navigable space (zoom, reveal, collapse)",
      "level": 4,
      "align": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "viewport": {
          "amount": 0.2
        },
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "duration": 0.5,
            "delay": 0.08
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "b-hurts": {
      "type": "elementRichText",
      "content": "### When Motion Hurts\n\n- **Decorative entrance animation** on every page load adds latency to the reading task without communicating meaning\n- **Parallax effects** that have no semantic relationship to content create visual noise\n- **Simultaneous animations** compete for attentional resources\n- **Long durations** on frequent UI events (button press → result) accumulate into noticeable friction\n- **Prefers-reduced-motion ignored** — vestibular disorders aside, motion that cannot be disabled disrespects the user",
      "level": 4,
      "align": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "viewport": {
          "amount": 0.2
        },
        "entranceMotion": {
          "transition": {
            "duration": 0.5,
            "delay": 0.08
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
